.Dd March 17, 2026
.Dt CONTACTCTL 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm contactctl
.Nd administration utility for contactd
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm user
.Aq Cm add Ns | Ns Cm list Ns | Ns Cm delete Ns | Ns Cm passwd
.Op Ar flags ...
.Nm
.Cm export
.Op Ar flags ...
.Nm
.Cm import
.Op Ar flags ...
.Ar file-or-dir
.Nm
.Cm version
.Op Fl -format Ar text Ns | Ns Ar json
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
manages users and imports/exports vCards for
.Xr contactd 8 .
It operates directly on the SQLite database and does not require
.Nm contactd
to be running.
.Pp
.Nm
may be invoked as a standalone binary or as a symlink to the
.Nm contactd
binary.
.Sh COMMANDS
.Ss user add
Create a user account.
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width Ds -compact
.It Fl -username Ar name
Username (required).
.It Fl -password Ar pass
Password (avoid on shared systems; prefer
.Fl -password-stdin ) .
.It Fl -password-stdin
Read password from standard input, one line.
.It Fl d , Fl -db-path Ar path , Fl -db Ar path
Database path.
.El
.Ss user list
List all users.
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width Ds -compact
.It Fl -format Ar table Ns | Ns Ar json
Output format.
Default:
.Cm table .
.It Fl d , Fl -db-path Ar path , Fl -db Ar path
Database path.
.El
.Ss user delete
Delete a user by username or numeric ID.
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width Ds -compact
.It Fl -username Ar name
Select user by username.
.It Fl -id Ar n
Select user by numeric ID.
.It Fl d , Fl -db-path Ar path , Fl -db Ar path
Database path.
.El
.Ss user passwd
Update a user's password.
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width Ds -compact
.It Fl -username Ar name
Select user by username.
.It Fl -id Ar n
Select user by numeric ID.
.It Fl -password Ar pass
New password.
.It Fl -password-stdin
Read new password from standard input.
.It Fl d , Fl -db-path Ar path , Fl -db Ar path
Database path.
.El
.Ss export
Export an addressbook's vCards.
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width Ds -compact
.It Fl -username Ar name
User whose addressbook is exported (required).
.It Fl -book Ar slug
Addressbook slug.
Default:
.Cm contacts .
.It Fl -format Ar dir Ns | Ns Ar concat
Output format.
.Cm dir
writes one
.Pa <href>.vcf
file per card into
.Fl -out ;
.Cm concat
writes concatenated vCards to stdout or
.Fl -out .
Default:
.Cm dir .
.It Fl -out Ar path
Output directory
.Pq Cm dir
or file
.Pq Cm concat .
Required for
.Cm dir
format.
.It Fl -dry-run
Validate and summarize without writing any files.
.It Fl d , Fl -db-path Ar path , Fl -db Ar path
Database path.
.El
.Ss import
Import vCards into an addressbook.
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width Ds -compact
.It Fl -username Ar name
User whose addressbook receives the import (required).
.It Fl -book Ar slug
Addressbook slug.
Default:
.Cm contacts .
.It Fl -dry-run
Parse and validate without writing to the database.
Advisory only: concurrent writes by
.Nm contactd
can alter the real import result.
.It Fl d , Fl -db-path Ar path , Fl -db Ar path
Database path.
.It Ar file-or-dir
Source path (required).
If a directory, all
.Pa *.vcf
files are imported and the filename becomes the CardDAV href.
If a file, concatenated vCards are parsed and each card's
.Dq UID
field becomes the href
.Pq Ar UID Ns Pa .vcf .
.El
.Ss version
Print version information and exit.
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width Ds -compact
.It Fl -format Ar text Ns | Ns Ar json
Output format.
Default:
.Cm text .
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It 0
Success.
.It 1
Runtime or I/O error.
.It 2
Usage or configuration error.
.It 3
Not found (e.g.\& unknown user or addressbook).
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Create a user, reading the password from stdin:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
printf '%s\en' 'secret' | contactctl user add --username alice --password-stdin
.Ed
.It
List all users as JSON:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
contactctl user list --format json
.Ed
.It
Change a user's password:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
printf '%s\en' 'newpass' | contactctl user passwd --username alice --password-stdin
.Ed
.It
Export an addressbook to a directory:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
contactctl export --username alice --format dir --out ./backup
.Ed
.It
Preview an import without writing:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
contactctl import --username alice --dry-run ./backup
.Ed
.It
Import a concatenated vCard file:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
contactctl import --username alice contacts.vcf
.Ed
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr contactd 8
